<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4416755>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 4. Hughjonestrongylus alisoni sp. n. In all illustrations of the synlophe in transverse section the dorsal aspect of the body is oriented towards the top of the page and the left side of the nematode to the left of the page. The dorsal and ventral (numbers with superscripts) ridges are numbered, as are the lateral rays of the bursa (right rays with superscripts). A. Female, anterior end lateral view; B. Male, mid body transverse section; C. Male, cervical end lateral view; D. Male, bursa dorsal lobe, not completely rolled flat; E. Female, posterior end lateral view; F. Male, bursa left lobe; G. Male, gubernaculum and spicule tip lateral view; H. Male, spicules, anterior end; I. Male, spicule tips; J. Male, bursa right lobe. Scale bars in µm: A, 100; B, C, F, G, H, I, J, 25; D, E, 50." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4416755/files/figure.png" .

